^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One other general play technique for Roberta. In general, when you are running a suit, proper technique is to play the honors in the shorter hand first. So, at trick two, in hearts, you play the King of hearts first, as that is the short hand  and in diamonds, in trick three, you play the Ace first, as that is the short hand. The reason for that is that it makes it harder to block the suit. |
PG| ***** 72 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I am just giving you the general technique. There are many reasons to deviate but you need to purposely deviate. In diamonds, actually, the correct play is the K of diamonds first, since then you can pick up 4 to the J in either hand. But, the general technique of unblocking honors from the short hand is still right most of the time.|
