Always count your quick tricks. Why is this essential? Counting your quick tricks helps you:|
PG| ***** 131 ***** |


AT|

• Appreciate the true value of Aces and Kings.|
PG| ***** 132 ***** |


AT|

• Distinguish between "good points" and "schmoints."|
PG| ***** 133 ***** |


AT|

• Appreciate that the value of all honor cards is greater when in combination with other honors.|
PG| ***** 134 ***** |


AT|

• Make good bidding decisions, such as:
1. ^cDeciding whether to open a borderline hand.
   ^CAvoid opening a marginal hand in first or second seat with fewer than two quick tricks.
2. ^CAvoiding penalty doubles based only on having "a lot of points."
3. ^CKnowing when it is correct to open 2@C.
